  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Transcranial electrical stimulation (TES) techniques offer a novel treatment approach for
      depression and have shown promising efficacy. However, there is no published data to date on
      their effectiveness as a maintenance treatment. This study will investigate ways of using TES
      as a maintenance treatment to prevent relapse in depression.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
